name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
Very nice long walkway and great that it is at my neighborhood. It can get crowded at times so do watch out. Some parts of the walkway is a bit narrow and the cyclists can be quite fast so for young families, keep a watch on the young children.

Great for the morning or evening walks.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: A nice park & long path way. Fit for everyone who look up for a walking/running track. It has fresh air since smokings are prohibited in this park. In the morning it doesn't too crowded

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Awesome view and awesome place to walk. You can go longest you want it shortest. Me and wife like to visit the place, whenever we have time and waterway mall is just on the way so you could grab quick bites if you feel like.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: It is an amazing Trip for Cycling, Jogging, walking etc. It has park Connector, like Park to Park, Park to Beach (Punggol Beach) etc. It is a 24 hours duration. You can try to visit your awesome park!

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: It’s a nice place for walk, jog and run. It’s picturesque and scenic. We almost walked till Coney Islands but night fall made it difficult, so had to get back.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Our family with the 1.5-2 year old baby enjoyed the walk and play in this park a lot. Fresh air, lots of tree and along the waterway.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Family friendly facilities with lush greenery. Well paved cycling routes around (minus the Coney Island stretch). Good for bird spotting and even fishing

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: This beautiful park runs along both sides of the waterway and is brimming with beautiful plants and wildlife, from otters and birds to monitor lizards and tortoises. There are well-maintained pathways for walking and cycling, but the routes are good for rollerblading and skateboarding too. Links to waterway point, sengkang, pasir ris, punggol beach and more.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Awesome scenic place for walk, jog or cycling. Be there early to enjoy the cool morning breeze, treaupitic waterway and pretty flowers too.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
Most beautiful park in Singapore I must say. Coney Island is just around the corner.
The whole area is large enough to accommodate quite a number of people. This will ensure some form of social distancing.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
Big and spacious park , very well developed.
PCN road in the park as well.
Make sure u keep with ur line/direction to avoid any accident as early morning can see alots of ppls exercise there already.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Good place to relax. It's  a park connector track, so expect cyclists. To also expect some of them speed and some who don't know how to read signs on bridges that clearly prohibit cycling. Other than these inconsiderate users, it's a nice place.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
A great recreational space for exercise, picnics and other outdoor activities! And some areas offer picturesque views that make you feel like you're overseas, especially in the early morning and dusk.

If you're lucky enough, you can get really close to some beautiful species of birds. There's also a good balance of areas exposed to sunlight and shade, so there's always a shady place to rest that's not too far away.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Good place for a walk or run.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Very nice park for relaxing or exercising. It's still nice although much green space has been eaten up by developments over the years, reducing nature to slivers of green between HDBs instead of the lush park it once was.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
Amazing park!
Cycling, jogging, running, leisure walk, breeze walk.
You can also have picnic there!

Love the place because of the calm atmosphere and scenery view.
Bring kids and family here.
Near SAFRA Punggol to swim, gym and eat.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Nice place to bring the kids, bike rental at Punggol SAFRA is convenient and easy access to the park. Pathways are relatively easy for children although can get crowded depending on the time. There are also toilets and water coolers situated along the route, and playgrounds nearer the housing estate for kids.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
Though quite far away from the city center, a nice decent place to go and get a good workout done. Great for the people who live nearby.

I especially go here to log in morning runs.

Presently construction is going around the area, so some parts are partially closed.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Nice place for a walk!! New punggol regional sport centre in progress. So looking forward to it. :)

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: The park is a nice walking sppt in the punggol area but Punggol park is much-much nicer. The kids water playground is very-very small and it was closed. The mall and the surrounding restaurants and coffees are a nice spot for the weekends.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Great place for couples to jog, young families to have an afternoon walk, small kids to play sand / water, elders to walk and relax, relatives and friends to picnic and fly kites! Just be careful when you bring young kids as there are lots of bicycles & scooters with quite high speed.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Nice park with a nice canal. This is the best place in Punggol for walks, jogs and runs. It is a beautiful park filled with people young and old. View of the canal is very nice and the natural wind by the canal is pleasing. This park is good for chilling out, working out and family bonding.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: This is an amazing place to walk through. Start in the morning, at about 7:00 am, and catch the beautiful sunrise as it slowly casts its light on the world around you. This is about THE BEST TIME to take photographs. You will be amazed at what you produce. Use the track as your guide, just walk on, not forgetting to look all around, so as not to miss the big and little things that matter. Just enjoy the myriad postcard  moments, and you will b e left with a sense of awe, greatness and respect for the world, and Mother Nature. Keep your ears open too for the many bird calls you’ll hear. You will feel rejuvenated and alive!

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Very nice, clean and serene park that you can jog, cycle and walk along the river.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: The park was beautiful and serene albeit the construction work’s happening around it. But once you follow along the trail to Coney Island, you’ll be entering a land of serenity and sometimes planes flying by!

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
Love the morning sunrise view.. Jogging or running must take picture here.

Sunrise around 7am - 710am. Must catch the right time. Posted pictures is taken on different day..

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Cool view of the lake, was on the road for abit, although I got lost. Has stuff like a public toilet and benches everywhere! It’s a great place to cycle with your friends and family, just make sure to practice safety!

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Good place to go with kids. You can play with sand, please be informed that currently water play area is under maintenance. Expected to open again in December. You should carry some snacks, as there’s no shop inside.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Beautiful place for jogging / running. Perfect for starting your weekend morning! So glad to live right next to it.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Great outdoor get away with the family. Really able to keep the kids away from the digital devices and get them outdoor here.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: A very scenic town to stay. Everything looks clean, neat and relaxing feel in the environment

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Great scenic place to cycle and walk, from here all the way to Lorong Halus Bridge.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Part of morning walk from Sunrise Bridge to Jewel Bridge🚶‍♀️👣really a hot day that make me sweat alot 🥵

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Beautiful and very long and large area to walk or jog anytime of the day.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Monitor lizards comes out for daily walk around 7 in morning and otters 🦦 have been spotted playing and eating fish near Sunrise Bridge. Plenty of seats around for people to chill and watch the stars at night and SAFRA along the park to get your MacDonalds or Mala Hot Pot

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: A fairly small park built around a waterway. Not many open spaces or dense trees - mostly flat walking paths and some seating areas by the waterside. May not be the best spot for bird photography due to the high human traffic and sparse trees

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Been here for evening jogging and Cycling. Very nice view. Not far from Sunrise bridge you can find toilet and vending machine.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Nice park for jogging, cycling or just to capture some photo

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Not crowded greens place for cycling or jogging along the park. The lorong halu wetland red bridge connected to puggol waterway park.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: One of best place to visit to Singapore. So greeny, freely walk

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
It's incredible how the Singapore government managed to transform this hinterland to such a beautiful neighbourhood.

Waterway is a quaint, safe, serene, and beautiful park for almost anyone. You can cycle, jog, scoot, or take a relaxing walk down this beauty. Given the dense nature landscape, it is incredibly cooling even without any strong breeze.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Love the tranquility here. A relatively big place for a very good walkout!

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Well connected by PCN, breezy and good seaviews. Reward yourselves for F&B and spend quality times with many outdoor activities with your loved ones !

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
The 4.2km waterway will traverse Punggol Town, Punggol Promenade and link up the reservoirs at Sungei Punggol and Sungei Serangoon to form a huge water reservoir.

Punggol Waterway Park is located along Sentul Crescent Road covering an area of 12.25 Hectares. This multi-purpose park is free from the bustling traffic and set in a serene lush greenery setting to serve the residents and visitors. Just few minutes away from the Punggol Town Centre, visitors will experience a nostalgic feel of the Old Punggol and the upcoming waterfront park.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Bright, colourful and vibrant spot with plenty room to cycle, exercise and stroll. Waterway path is a delight to stroll on. Adventure bridge is a delighful photo spot.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Lovely serene views and feel. Great for walks or cycling.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Beautiful place to jog and cycle. You can admire the water, greenery and the nice man-made structures

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Sunset timing, so colour a bit yellow, out of no where to go in Singapore for relax outdoor activities? You should just try this! Cycling along the river, it's quite nice. Accompany by the nature sounds. Awesome.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Nice walk..many F&Bs..got toilets for walkers !

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: For fresh and peaceful walk in the natural. One of the best option, just maybe crowded during weekends

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:

Got some nice paintings on the wall you can take photo too!

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
Punggol Promenade - Great Park Connector Network for Cycling. From here, you can cycle to the entrance of Coney Island, about 1 km only.

Don't own a bicycle, no problem. Rent a bicycle from Obike (download from Apple App Store or Android Play Store) at SGD1 per 30 minutes. Want more choices of rides, walk down to Jomando Adventure & Recreations.

name: Punggol Waterway Park

review_text: One-of-a-kind place in Singapore, it is so beautiful and well designed that it can be considered an attraction. So many spots for that amazing photo. The place is also near a few malls for that after-cycling meal.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
Gone to check out the Punggol Waterway Park Dog Run (12 Mar 2022). Not opened yet.
Place is quite big, maybe slightly bigger than a quarter football field. Right by the entrance is a wash area with water tap.

Surrounding area is serene and good for an evening walk.

Those driving there, park at Car Park A (refer to photo), follow the foot path leftwards and you should spot the fenced up area.
Hope to visit again once it opens.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: A good park to walk/run/cycle during the early morning or evening hours. Not a very sheltered walking area hence don't really recommend going during the afternoon or you would risk getting burnt.  The paved walking path makes it a comfortable walk that wouldn't overwork the knees

name: Punggol Waterway Park

name: Punggol Waterway Park

name: Punggol Waterway Park

name: Punggol Waterway Park

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Very pretty. Love the atmosphere. A mix of clean, new amenities, and lush greenery and waterways. Some bars and restaurants with nice lights and music in the evening. A bit off the beaten path from the city center, but maybe that makes it even nicer when you're there

name: Punggol Waterway Park

name: Punggol Waterway Park

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
Great big park around Punggol but honestly would give 5 stars if they fixed certain areas that tend to be flooded after a rain. Great park for strolling, running, cycling.

Need to learn to navigate a bit because if you end up on the wrong side, you might end up not getting where you want to go. For example Waterway Point may be right in front of you but you're on the opposite side so you need to find the next nearest bride to cross over, which may not be that near at all, especially if you're cycling.

It's a smaller park than we were expecting, but it does have paths on both sides of the water ideal which are all ideal for exercising. Also has a playground which is pretty good, and a cool suspension bridge you can walk over too.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Really lovely place with great scenery

name: Punggol Waterway Park

Clean and fresh air

Green and full of trees which is good for people want to do exercise even evening time.

They maintain the cleanliness every day.

Nice for walking and relaxation

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Too many construction activity along the waterway compared to when I last visited the place some years ago. The SAFRA building is monstrous and ugly. You go to a park to enjoy nature, why have all these man made structures.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Collected 2 scan for 365 health. Great for cycling but not so great for sunny day walk. Will be great for evening walk. There is a water park for family with children and bring extra clothes for change.

name: Punggol Waterway Park

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Really nice park, it is linked to many residential buildings and have a designed jogging and cycling path which makes the place a whole lot safer. There are alsong restaurants alongside the pavement and also bikes available for rent. Really do suggest this place for everyone to check out, nice sunsets too!!

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Suitable for cycling and jogging.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Very run down. Trees overgrown. All the play area for kids closed. There are huge construction going on around the park. Adventure bridge is really tiny. Only good thing is that it’s a short distance to Waterway mall and Safra Punggol where are many eateries, activities, and shopping.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Scenic and very wide open area to walk. Great place to take walks with family or loved one(s). There is a public restroom with a vending machine, water cooler and outdoor water-themed playground near the middle of the park. Adventure bridge is also a great spot to take photos. Bring enough water and comfortable shoes. There is a mall nearby where you can rest and relax after a long walk.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: A fast developed complex in the north suburbs of Singapore.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
Not a dense and lush park, more like a stretch of green intersecting the concrete high rises. Facilities include toilets, a sand playground and a normal playground. Not exactly teeming with wildlife but expect to find a few fishes and birds.

Very clean and well maintained as well as close to Waterway Point shopping mall. Can visit the fountain for a show at night.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: A nice place for jogging and walking. When it is windy feels so pleasant. Track is shared with bicycles so not fully safe for kids.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Nice little park with trails that connect to others in the area. There is a splashpad nearby for kids (or adults). There are places to rent bikes since the trails can take a while if you plan to do them all. Make sure to take lots of water if you plan to go!

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Great place for walks and cycling.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: A great hiking path for families

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
Plenty of seafood restaurants and other eateries for a family friendly area! The space allows kids to be kids while the parents enjoy the breeze and dinner. The horseback riding club located here lends the area an interesting rustic feel.

Issue is the place is not easily accessible.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Always love to have a walk or even simple picnic just to relax :)

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Great place to walk or chill out in the East. The park is quie big with nice scenery. There's a lot of people exercising, especially after 6pm, but not too crowded. Also, it's a nice place to catch Pokemon here.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Just moved in and was amazed on the outcome. Beautiful and serene with wide open spaces for various outdoor leisure activities. And the choices of food are incredible.   It feels good to be far from city life. The value of flats are going to skyrocket in the future.

name: Punggol Waterway Park

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Love it. It's beautiful and teeming with people young and old exercising. The perfect place to go for a morning jog and end the day strolling down the waterway. Avoid going in the afternoon as the outdoor heat can be uncomfortable during the day.

name: Punggol Waterway Park

name: Punggol Waterway Park

name: Punggol Waterway Park

name: Punggol Waterway Park

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Easily accessible from sengkang through 136,82,83. A mall with great food joints and shopping places.

name: Punggol Waterway Park

Worth exploring if you fancy a stroll or jog somewhere green in Singers.

name: Punggol Waterway Park

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text: Developed with the theme "Family Leisure", this park has many facilities to cater to the young and old . The play and fitness equipment for active recreation, open lawn areas for picnics or kite flying, a wooded area for leisurely strolls, a plaza area for taiqi and a community corner for relaxing can be enjoyed by all members of the family. The park has two distinctive zones, i.e, the Southern Active Zone where the features for major activities are provided, and the densely forested area in the north of the pond, which forms the "Passive Zone" where one can engage in passive form of recreation.

name: Punggol Waterway Park

Enjoy it now before more concrete buildings spring up along the waterway.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
The mall provides for all shopping needs. There is DAISO as well. The air-con is cold enough, if you stay within the premises. If you have kids, try the 🐎 round about circus ride and the Choo-Choo train ride.

Also a delightful place for a casual long walk as there are many shades around the PCN. Be prepared to see monitor lizards, white-breasted waterhen, colorful birds and of course fishes. If you have time, try to observe how the water way is designed to "behave" and stay evergreen.

name: Punggol Waterway Park
review_text:
A nice and beautiful serenic park.It consist of a huge park covering a big area.Also incoperated a man made canal linking the Serangoon Reservoir ( Formally the Serangoon River ) in the east to the Punggol Reservoir ( Formally the Punggol River ) in the west.Along the canal are walking/jogging
and cylcing/biking tracks.The cycling/biking tracks are link to the Serangoon Park Connector and Punggol Park Connector.Sundays can more people enjoying themselves engaging in different activies there.The park is quite breezy at the end of the year when the North-
East Monsoon Winds arrives.It is a nice place to spent a days off on Sundays in the late afternoon when it is cooler.
